petitive overlaps, disagreement, and third-party complaints in casual ELF conversations among friends. In doing so, the notion of cooperativeness is re-examined, and the appropriateness of an intercultural approach to analyzing multimodal resources in ELF interactions is demonstrated.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 02. Mai 2023) 4aLingua Franca. 4aMultimodalität. 4aSoziolinguistik. 4aUmgangssprache. 4aZwischenmenschliche Beziehung. 7aLANGUAGE ARTS & DISCIPLINES / Linguistics / General.2bisacsh  aCasual Conversations.  aConflict Talk.  aEnglish as a Lingua Franca.  aIntercultural Approach.  aMultimodal Conversation Analysis.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus DeG Package 2023 Part 1z978311117578208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDe Gruyter Mouton eBook Package 2023z97831112057930 cEPUBz97815015128890 cprintz978150151781540uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978150151296440uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781501512964423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781501512964/original  a978-3-11-117578-2  DG Plus DeG Package 2023 Part 1b2023  a978-3-11-120579-3  De Gruyter Mouton eBook Package 2023b2023  aEBA_CL_LS  aEBA_CL_SN  aEBA_DGALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_LS  aEBA_ECL_SN  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK